"title": "6213: participation, in sin",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6213",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The natural condition of all human beings as a result of sharing in Adam's fall. Believers are called not to associate with, nor give approval to wickedness but to stand apart from evil as God's holy people.</p>\n<h2>Participation in Adam</h2>\n<h3>In Adam's humanity</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:20\">GEN 3:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen5:1-Gen5:3\">GEN 5:1–5:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:6\">JHN 3:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:26\">ACT 17:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:48-1Cor15:49\">1CO 15:48–15:49</a></p>\n<h3>In Adam's sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:12\">ROM 5:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:7\">HOS 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:15-Rom5:19\">ROM 5:15–5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:21-1Cor15:22\">1CO 15:21–15:22</a>GEN <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:17\">3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:20-Rom8:21\">ROM 8:20–8:21</a></p>\n<h3>In a sinful nature</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:3\">EPH 2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:5\">ROM 7:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:14-Rom7:20\">ROM 7:14–7:20</a></p>\n<h2>Ways of participating in evil</h2>\n<h3>Associating with evildoers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps50:18\">PSA 50:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:6\">GEN 49:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:31\">LEV 15:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:12-Josh23:13\">JOS 23:12–23:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job34:8\">JOB 34:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:4\">PSA 141:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov22:24-Prov22:25\">PRO 22:24–22:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:10-2John1:11\">2JN 1:10–1:11</a> <em>giving hospitality to evildoers</em></p>\n<h3>Giving approval to evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:17\">LEV 19:17</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:5\">PSA 64:5</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:32\">ROM 1:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:28-2Sam3:29\">2SA 3:28–3:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:37\">2SA 3:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps49:13\">PSA 49:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek13:22\">EZK 13:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:48\">LUK 11:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:60\">ACT 7:60</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:20\">ACT 22:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:22\">ROM 14:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:11\">EPH 5:11</a></p>\n<h3>Sacrifice and idolatry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num25:1-Num25:3\">NUM 25:1–25:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:33\">2KI 17:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:17\">HOS 4:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:18-1Cor10:20\">1CO 10:18–10:20</a></p>\n<h2>God's people are not to participate in evil</h2>\n<h3>God's people are called to be holy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:26\">LEV 20:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44-Lev11:45\">LEV 11:44–11:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:2\">LEV 19:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:15–1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Separation from foreign gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:7\">JOS 23:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:30\">DEU 12:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:18\">DEU 29:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:2\">1KI 11:2</a></p>\n<h3>Separation from the godless</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:11\">EZR 10:11</a></strong> <em>Too close an association with the nations round about, particularly in marriage, would cause Israel to compromise her unique relationship with God</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:14\">2CO 6:14</a></strong> <em>Often related to marriage, this applies to all close alliances with unbelievers.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra4:1-Ezra4:3\">EZR 4:1–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:1-Ezra9:2\">EZR 9:1–9:2</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:4\">REV 18:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra10:2\">EZR 10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:20\">NEH 2:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:30\">NEH 10:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:26-Neh13:27\">NEH 13:26–13:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:45\">JER 51:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:39\">1CO 7:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:17\">2CO 6:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:11\">ISA 52:11</a></p>\n<h3>Separation from evildoers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:22\">1TI 5:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:17\">ROM 16:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:9-1Cor5:11\">1CO 5:9–5:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess3:14\">2TH 3:14</a></p>",
